race.comment: MAGICAL SEQUENCE (3) stepped up to 1400m last start in a CL5 and was just fair when the race favourite. Back to 1200m here and she gets Pike back in the saddle. Looked to be trending the right way prior to her last start and she appears the main danger. MAI ALOHA (4) flew home first-up when 0.9L off the winner at Bunbury when a $1.70 favourite. The wide draw is a niggle, though the rise in trip should suit and with a touch of luck, she'll be right in the finish. CHAMPAGNE CRUSADER (7) can improve on the first-up effort with CJP replacing the apprentice hoop. MAIN ACT (1) will find this a little easier than his first-up effort and he can put his best foot forward.
